CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 27, 1955, pg. 16, reads: "The R. Johnsons - One of Homestead's most progressive families is the Robert Johnsons of Glenn Street. From his mill earnings Mr. Johnson who retired after forty years of service built the family eight room brick house and moved in in 1917. Ten children were born to the couple, and eight are still living and making contributions to the areas in which they live. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boy wearing striped shirt, Mrs. Johnson, and Robert Johnson standing outside their home, 1208 Glenn Street, Homestead
